2013-11-21	Denilson Figueiredo de Sá <denilsonsa@gmail.com>

	* === Released 1.7 ===
	* Note: This release has a few backward-incompatible names! Be careful
	while updating.
	* parse_files.inc.php, check_servers.sh: Plaintext log files that will be
	served via Apache now have .txt suffix.
	* parse_files.inc.php, check_servers.sh: Renamed last_log to
	last_global_log, last_success to last_success_date, last_test to
	last_test_date.
	* server_list-sample.conf: Improved documentation, specifying the valid
	chars for the id column.
	* check_servers.sh: Making sure the log dir is created before accessing
	it. Prevents some errors on first run.

2013-11-20	Denilson Figueiredo de Sá <denilsonsa@gmail.com>

	* INSTALL: Renamed to INSTALL.md.
	* README: Renamed to README.md.
	* TODO.txt: Renamed to TODO.md.

2013-11-20	Denilson Figueiredo de Sá <denilsonsa@gmail.com>

	* === Released 1.6 ===
	* parse_files.inc.php: Added date_default_timezone_set(). Removes a PHP
	warning.
	* parse_files.inc.php: Changed the download link to GitHub and BitBucket
	repositories.
	* parse_files.inc.php: Added trim() to the lines read from the conf file.
	Fixes a silly error when parsing empty lines.
	* index.php: Fixed an error when a server exists in last_log but not in
	the conf file.
	* server_list-sample.conf: Added column documentation at the sample conf
	file.
	* INSTALL: Improved the installation instructions and reformatted the text
	to Markdown conventions.
	* README: Added a README file.
	* LICENSE: Chosen MIT as the license for this project.

2010-12-27	Denilson Figueiredo de Sá <denilsonsa@gmail.com>

	* === Released 1.5 ===
	* all PHP files: Changed short tags <?=something?> to long tags <?php echo
	something ?>.
	* all PHP files: Changed charset from ISO-8859-1 to UTF-8.

2008-10-20	Denilson Figueiredo de Sá <denilsonsa@gmail.com>

	* === Released 1.4 ===
	* ChangeLog: Manually wrote this file. Don't ask me about what has changed
	in older versions, I don't remember. ;)
	* check_servers.sh(check_http): Updated the wget SINGLE_LINE_OUTPUT
	filter. The old filter was somewhat broken in new wget versions.
	* check_servers.sh: Using LC_ALL=C inside this script. No, I don't plan to
	add support to multiple languages.

